module blink.mojom;

// Do not remove items from, or reorder this enum as it is used in histograms.
// New items should be added at the end.
// Permission status is used in the permission infrastructure to express whether
// a permission as queried is granted, denied, can be prompted for upon
// returning from the query, or has unsatisfied options (semantically similar to
// denied, but a downgraded request may yield a grant. Possible use cases:
// coarse geolocation may be granted while precise geolocation is denied --> a
// request for precise may return UNSATISFIED_OPTIONS, which may cause the
// permission to downgrade the request to a coarse request). A permission
// request may trigger a prompt and will return a PermissionStatus upon
// returning by passing it to the registered BrowserPermissionCallback. However,
// a PermissionStatus can be queried without requesting it.
enum PermissionStatus {
  GRANTED,
  DENIED,
  ASK,
  UNSATISFIED_OPTIONS,
  LAST = UNSATISFIED_OPTIONS
};
